  "texts": [
    "This challenge persists across all LLM-based completion paradigms (prompting, masking, seq2seq) despite their semantic richness.",
    "requires exhaustive text processing and candidate scoring, which can be computationally expensive in large KGs (Wang B. et al., 2021; Ren et al., 2024).",
    "While multi-task learning approaches [MT-DNN (Choi and Ko, 2023), LP-BERT (Li et al., 2023) ] attempt to share computational overhead across tasks, the fundamental scalability gap persists-especially in large-scale KGs where latency grows polynomially with graph density (Heim et al., 2025).",
    "This creates an unresolved tension between LLMs' semantic richness and traditional methods' operational efficiency. 3.",
    "Challenges in prompt engineering: Current prompt engineering approaches [ProLINK (Wang K. et al., 2024), TAGREAL (Jiang P. et al., 2023) ] for knowledge graph completion exhibit several key limitations."
  ],
